HEADWORD: Ricinolein
<hw>Ric`in*o"le*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ricinus</ets> castor-oil plant + <ets>oleum</ets> oil.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The glycerin salt of ricinoleic acid, occuring
as a characteristic constituent of castor oil; -- formerly called
<altname>palmin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ricinolic</ent>⟦br⟧
